{"key":"processedPost-15863142","value":{"id":15863142,"first":15829388,"last":16048907,"when":1330222620,"utime":"02/26/12 04:17 AM","content":"I'd have fruited them uncased.&nbsp; Bulk substrates don't really benefit much from a casing.<br /><br />Next time, colonize substrates that size at around 65F to 70F.&nbsp; You'll get 10 to 15 degrees of heating in the substrate, and that puts it up around 100F, which is more likely to ruin them.&nbsp; Any substrate temperature over 82F slows down colonization, so keep that in mind.&nbsp; The ambient air temp should never be 85F, even with small brf cakes.<br />RR","title":"Re: Spawn running on bulk substrate"}}